"description_plain":"","submitter_user":"lvmbdv","user_is_author":true,"tags":["hardware","networking","security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qwk5vn","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qwk5vn/building_passive_ethernet_tap"},{"short_id":"cmeyvt","created_at":"2026-07-01T05:23:11.000-05:00","title":"EmacsWiki Blog Carnival \"Programming\"","url":"https://plaindrops.de/blog/2026/emacscarnival2607/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"tusharhero","user_is_author":false,"tags":["emacs","programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cmeyvt","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cmeyvt/emacswiki_blog_carnival_programming"},{"short_id":"w01x4p","created_at":"2026-07-01T05:22:06.000-05:00","title":"Which GitHub features are needed in a code forge before you can migrate?","url":"","score":5,"flags":0,"comment_count":11,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWhich GitHub features would you consider a blocker for migrating to a different code forge, and in what order do you prioritize them?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eContext:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am heads down building a code forge (\u003ca href=\"https://juju.bi\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://juju.bi\u003c/a\u003e) based on three ideas:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCode collaboration part should work offline\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eShould be compatible with GitHub API (like how some services are considered S3 compatible)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSupport \u003ccode\u003echange-id\u003c/code\u003e based features (ex: Jujutsu's evolog)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI shipped a super-early version that I am currently dogfooding. \u003ca href=\"https://juju.bi/changelog/2026-07-01-alpha-release\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://juju.bi/changelog/2026-07-01-alpha-release\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am currently focused on improving the experience for small teams working on private repos. I would like to polish the overall product before thinking about public repos. (A lot of great forges exist for public repos right now).\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Which GitHub features would you consider a blocker for migrating to a different code forge, and in what order do you prioritize them?\r\n\r\n**Context:**\r\n\r\nI am heads down building a code forge (https://juju.bi) based on three ideas:\r\n\r\n* Code collaboration part should work offline\r\n* Should be compatible with GitHub API (like how some services are considered S3 compatible)\r\n* Support `change-id` based features (ex: Jujutsu's evolog)\r\n\r\nI shipped a super-early version that I am currently dogfooding. https://juju.bi/changelog/2026-07-01-alpha-release\r\n\r\nI am currently focused on improving the experience for small teams working on private repos. I would like to polish the overall product before thinking about public repos. (A lot of great forges exist for public repos right now).","submitter_user":"pksunkara","user_is_author":true,"tags":["vcs"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/w01x4p","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/w01x4p/which_github_features_are_needed_code"},{"short_id":"d6tl13","created_at":"2026-07-01T05:22:01.000-05:00","title":"Teaching digiKam to Understand You: Natural Language Search with Local LLMs","url":"http://srirupa19.github.io/gsoc/2026/06/28/gsoc1.html","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchonborn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/d6tl13","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/d6tl13/teaching_digikam_understand_you_natural"},{"short_id":"hv42hz","created_at":"2026-07-01T04:39:07.000-05:00","title":"Ditching Claude for OpenCode and OpenRouter","url":"https://www.ianwootten.co.uk/2026/07/01/ditching-claude-for-opencode-and-openrouter/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"raymii",